---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — Thanarak Kanyaprasit">
  <main class="legal">
    <article class="legal-inner">
      <header>
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="updated">Last updated: May 27, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Overview</h2>
        <p>
          This page exists for platform compliance for connected apps and
          experimental tools operated by Thanarak Kanyaprasit. It describes the
          limited data handling used to support authentication, account access,
          and basic service operation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>Depending on the app and permissions you approve, we may receive:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Basic profile identifiers needed to sign you in</li>
          <li>Email address, only when you explicitly grant that permission</li>
          <li>Minimal account metadata needed to keep the app functioning</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not intentionally collect sensitive personal information beyond
          what is required for the specific app feature you use.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To authenticate your account and keep you signed in</li>
          <li>To operate the requested feature or connected workflow</li>
          <li>To maintain reliability, diagnose failures, and prevent abuse</li>
          <li>To respond to support or deletion requests you send directly</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell personal information. Data may be processed by hosting,
          analytics, or infrastructure providers only when needed to operate the
          app, or disclosed when required by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain data only for as long as it is needed to operate the app,
          meet legal obligations, resolve disputes, or enforce security and
          abuse protections. You may request deletion at any time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Request access to data we hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction or deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Revoke third-party app permissions from the relevant provider settings</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Data Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          To request deletion of your data, email
          <a href="mailto:thanarak_ka@cmu.ac.th">thanarak_ka@cmu.ac.th</a>
          with the subject "Data Deletion Request". We will process the request
          within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Security</h2>
        <p>
          We apply reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect
          your information. No method of transmission over the Internet is 100%
          secure, however, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          These apps are not intended for children under 13. We do not
          knowingly collect personal data from children under 13.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be
          posted on this page with an updated revision date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For any questions about this Privacy Policy, contact:<br />
          <a href="mailto:thanarak_ka@cmu.ac.th">thanarak_ka@cmu.ac.th</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <footer class="legal-foot">
        <a href="/">← Back to home</a>
      </footer>
    </article>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 8rem) clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    color: #f4efe7;
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(214, 90, 58, 0.18), transparent 32%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #100d0b 0%, #181411 100%);
  }

  .legal-inner {
    max-width: 72ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-family: "Hanken Grotesk", system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0.55;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: "Instrument Serif", serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 1.5rem + 4vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .updated {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    opacity: 0.68;
    margin: 0 0 3.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: "Instrument Serif", serif;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  p,
  ul {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  li {
    margin: 0.25rem 0;
  }

  a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(244, 239, 231, 0.45);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: text-decoration-color 200ms ease;
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: currentColor;
  }

  .legal-foot {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(244, 239, 231, 0.12);
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
